comment_regular_data.body:
@numToStr I think your problem is more so with the `g@` operator rather than operator-pending mode in general. 
I tested with your comment plugin (by implementing the same logic as I did for yank) and the cursor position does get preserved (with `sticky = false` that is).
However, I don't know if this is a good idea because the `operatorfunc` called by `g@` could be anything, it could alter the text significantly (your plugin's changes to the text are minimal so it works pretty well). What's safe about yank is that we're 100% certain the text isn't changed.
